				<li id="16734232" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1657513786000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t530433/Blue-Tearstone-Ring" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">11 Jul 2022 00:29</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=165&p=16734232" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Did a test: to all the people saying it&apos;s a &quot;soft ToD&quot;, where an attack that would bring you below 20% health is also reduced by 20%; wherever you heard this, you are sorely mistaken. I was Lvl 79 with 27 vigor (1000 hp) and nothing other than the blue tearstone ring on (no absorption, 76 physical defense) vs. Champion Gundyr, no NG+ (or first run or whatever).<br/><br/>He has an attack where he takes a few short steps, then he brings his halberd directly on your forehead. In my setup, it does 516 damage, bringing me down to a total of 484. If the ring did in fact work like ToD, it would save me from being killed by this attack if hit by it a second time, and leave me with 71.2 health left: 516 * 0.2 (20%) = 103.2, 516 - 103.2 = 412.8, 484 - 412.8 = 71.2. It does not, however, and I die to the second hit. I did this test multiple times and saw absolutely no difference in the damage taken by the attacks. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16734232" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="colla