				<li id="16397785" class="cmnt-root" data="10" data-d="1640914523000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t530433/Blue-Tearstone-Ring" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">30 Dec 2021 20:35</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=165&p=16397785" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">After testing this ring thoroughly in a controlled environment where a Lloyd Shield Ring buff would prevent death but being hit at identical health with the Blue Tearstone Ring would not I can confidently confirm the ring does not work retroactively. This means the ring&apos;s defense increase is only applied after your health is below 20%. This means the ring is overall useless in the vast majority of situations. Any posts claiming retroactive damage prevention are wrong.<br/><br/>The attacks used for the tests were on NG7 and were Gael&apos;s phase 1 grab attack and Midir&apos;s opening fire breath. If you can provide any video proof of retroactive damage prevention please do so.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16397785" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16397785" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>10</p><i cla